******
Cases in various countries:
Asia
----
Cambodia (national). 25 Aug 2012. At least 27 590 dengue fever cases have been reported in more than 7 months of this year [2012], a 150 percent rise compared with 11 017 cases during the same period last year [2011], according to a report of the National Center for Parasitology, Entomology and Malaria Control released to the media on Saturday [25 Aug 2012]. The report said that since the start of the year [2012] to [20 Aug 2012], the disease had claimed 111 lives of children, up 131 percent compared with 48 deaths during the same period last year [2011].
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/health/2012-08/25/c_131807545.htm

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Cambodia can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1iGB. - Mod.TY]

- Pakistan (Lahore, Punjab province). 23 Aug 2012. A patient tested positive for the dengue virus at Mayo Hospital while 2 others are suspected of having contracted the virus.
http://tribune.com.pk/story/424911/dengue-resurfaces-man-tests-positive-2-suspected-cases/

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of Lahore can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1kdh. - Mod.TY]

- India (East Siang district, Arunachal Pradesh state). 25 Aug 2012. A team of scientists from the Regional Medical Research Centre at Dibrugarh in neighbouring Assam is visiting East Siang district of Arunachal Pradesh to conduct detailed investigation into the outbreak of dengue at Pasighat and its adjoining areas. Of 118 blood samples collected from Pasighat recently, 4 tested positive for dengue [virus infections].
http://www.business-standard.com/generalnews/news/teamscientists-to-investigate-outbreakdengue/48095/

[Maps of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and http://healthmap.org/r/1pSH. - Mod.TY]

- India (Bhandara district, Maharashtra state). 25 Aug 2012. The outbreak of dengue and chikungunya across the district, including Bhandara town, since the last 14 days is threatening to spread further. Around 1500 patients are taking treatment from private doctors in a week. Most of the patients are from rural areas.
http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-25/nagpur/33384803_1_dengue-and-chikungunya-private-doctors-platelets-count

[This is a mixed dengue and chikungunya outbreak, and there is no indication about numbers or relative proportions of each pathogen.

- India (West Bengal state). 23 Aug 2012. As many as 109 confirmed cases of dengue have been reported so far in West Bengal, a senior health official said Friday [17 Aug 2012]. When the endemic 1st came in force in the 2nd week of August 2012, the number of confirmed cases was 80.
http://twocircles.net/2012aug23/109_cases_dengue_bengal.html

- India (Bellary district, Karnataka state). 21 Aug 2012. Hospitals in the district have seen a sharp rise in the number of patients getting admitted with symptoms of dengue in recent days. People in the thousands, especially children, are showing symptoms of dengue like high fever, cough, fatigue, and body pain. Of the total 149 suspected dengue cases, 65 have tested positive and all the patients are undergoing treatment.
http://www.deccanherald.com/content/273276/dengue-cases-rise-bellary.html
